{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Iscrizioni Centuripine","Libertini","1949","\u003Cspan>Guido Libertini, «Iscrizioni Centuripine», \u003Ci>Siculorum Gymnasium\u003C/i> 2 (1949): 91–97\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/VQURX85J",[8,288,376,433,477,520,579],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":28,"handNote":37,"date":200,"places":205,"geo":214,"provenance":207,"provenanceGeo":218,"country":221,"region":222,"settlement":223,"repository":224,"idno":228,"textLang":231,"tmNumber":235,"facsimile":236,"letterHeights":243,"publications":258,"zotero":264,"keywords":270,"html":281,"bibl":282,"citedRangeSort":283,"languageSort":232,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic002945","A gymnasiarch crowns a group of youths",{"_":12},"edited",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":27},"#condition.fragment",{"layout":29},{"p":30,"rs":31,"damage":35},"15 neatly carved lines of Greek letters, of which the first four are larger. There appears to be a slight vacat at the top; lines 1-3 are indented by the equivalent of 1-2 characters at most; from line 4 onwards the left indentation increases, with clear vacats after lines 5 and 6, and a fixed left margin (c.7 cm vacat) from line 7 onwards; a vacat is consistently inserted between each name in the list from line 7 onwards.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":36},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":38,"dimensions":166},[39,40],"Elegant letters with minimal serifs/terminations visible on longer strokes (e.g. on tau, sigma and epsilon). Alpha has straight bar; beta has smaller upper loop, with the two loops connected without meeting the vertical; epsilon has shorter middle bar; theta is a full-size circle with a detached horizontal stroke at the centre; kappa has full length arms; mu has near vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes meeting a small way above the baseline; xsi is formed of vertical with three horizontals, the middle one of shorter length; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length vertical strokes; sigma has horizontal topo and bottom strokes; phi is ovoid, with vertical taller than other letters (14-15mm); omega full size, near circular, but open at the base. Traces of a secondary text include lunate epsilon (see commentary).",{"_":41,"ref":42},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                         